  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n\r\nI am not sure if it is bug or not, but the behaviour is kind weird, as shown in the working demo [here](https://stackblitz.com/edit/react-pa27iu?file=index.js).\r\n\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nThe current behaviour is that when I  render a dialog from onclick setstate callback, like this\r\n```\r\n<div onClick={()=>{\r\n  this.setState({\r\n    a : 1\r\n  }, ()=>{\r\n    this.renderPortal()\r\n  })\r\n}}> click me</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\nthis.renderPortal() will render the dialog, however, I cannot close the dialog. But when I do\r\n``` \r\n<div onClick={()=>{\r\n this.renderPortal()\r\n}}> click me</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\nI can close the dialog.\r\n\r\nIt seems that react thinks the Dialog rendered from setState callback is stateless, why is that?\r\n\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nShouldn't these two snippets work the same way?\r\n\r\n# #",
